1. Executive Summary & Product Vision
Reclaimng is an empathetic, enterprise-grade digital estate transition protocol built for the Nigerian financial ecosystem. The platform addresses systemic friction points within the e-Dividend Mandate Management System (e-DMMS) and commercial banking networks. It provides a secure digital bridge that validates legal beneficiaries via QoreID and automates the recovery and sweeping of unclaimed dividends and frozen bank assets of deceased individuals into a single, unified Estate Account.
1.1 Business Model & Revenue Capture
To drastically reduce the historical financial overhead associated with traditional estate management in Nigeria (where solicitors typically charge between 5% and 10% on top of an additional 10% state estate duty), Reclaimng standardizes flat premium pricing:
Platform Service Premium: Exactly 10% of the gross worth of all recovered assets processed through the transition pipeline.
Consent & Enforcement Mechanism: This fee structure is transparently disclosed and explicitly bound via a mandatory, un-bypassable legal confirmation check-box component prior to initiating any discovery phase.
