3. Detailed Screen Specifications & Functional Logic Mapping
3.1 auth.html (Intelligent Role Auto-Detect Engine)
User Interface: A singular, streamlined authentication card layout completely devoid of manual client-side role toggle selection switches.
Routing Logic Loop: The submission trigger on the primary button parses input credentials via a JavaScript routing routine:
Consumer Profiles: Auto-detects account metadata and routes the browser context instantly to dashboard.html.
Administrative Compliance Accounts: Auto-detects validation strings and routes the context instantly to admin-queue.html.
Visual Polish: Displays a brief 800ms text shimmer/spinner state on the button surface prior to routing to mimic secure token authorization layers.
3.2 dashboard.html (Consumer Portfolio & Historical Workspace)
Access Control: Enforces strict role access restrictions. Administrative accounts are barred from this interface.
Persistent Notification System: If an administrator approves a request via the compliance terminal, the user's dashboard container renders a prominent, persistent banner layout at the top of the screen:
🔔 System Notice: Your asset sweep has cleared. Access your Unified Estate Vault.
First-Time Login Empty State UI: If no historical cases are tied to the consumer profile, the workspace displays a minimalist layout consisting of an empty folder graphic placeholder, descriptive copy ("No active estate recoveries discovered"), and a primary Sage Green button labeled "Add Asset Recovery" which links directly to wizard.html.
Populated State UI Grid: If historical operations exist, the empty layout is replaced with a data grid containing real records alongside current status tags. Antigravity must populate this view with two sample items:
Item 1 (Historical Archive): Estate of Late Alice Bello — ₦5,000,000.00 | Status Badge: Settled (Emerald Green).
Item 2 (Active Operation): Estate of Late Samuel Bello — ₦12,450,000.00 | Status Badge: Pending Review (Amber Yellow).
3.3 wizard.html (Accordion-driven Recovery Engine & QoreID Gate)
UI Interaction Mechanics: Built as a vertical stack of four progressive accordion panels. Steps 2, 3, and 4 sit in collapsed, disabled states and expand sequentially only upon validation of the preceding step.
Step 1: Intake Surface: Captures Deceased Relative’s Legal Name, Date of Death Input, and 11-digit BVN field. Validation collapses Step 1 and opens Step 2.
Step 2: Probate Document Ingestion & QoreID Gate: A dashed file upload zone for Death Certificates and Letters of Administration.
The Asynchronous QoreID Gate: When documents are uploaded, clicking "Submit for Verification" triggers an intermediate full-screen glassmorphic processing modal overlay:
📁 Document Verification Processing: Your uploaded probate certificates have been securely routed to the QoreID Verification Node. We are cross-checking authenticity with the National Identity Management Commission (NIMC) and the High Court Probate Registry. You will be notified immediately upon clearance to proceed to Asset Discovery.
Verification Resolution: Once confirmed via mock interaction scripts, the modal closes, Step 2 visually compresses into a "Verified" success check state, and Step 3 is unlocked.
Step 3: Discovered Assets Matrix: Renders an itemized asset ledger summarizing balances discovered across NIBSS network nodes. Clicking "Verify Assets" unlocks Step 4.
Step 4: Settlement Authorization & Revenue Mandate: Displays a total consolidation valuation tracking at ₦12,450,000.00. Features an explicit billing confirmation line item detailing the flat 10% recovery processing commission fee.
The Legal Mandate Interaction Trigger: A mandatory check-box element tied to this functional text string:
▢ I hereby explicitly authorize Reclaimng to act as our digital transition proxy. I confirm that I have reviewed the platform Privacy Policy and Terms of Service, and agree to the standardized 10% platform service fee (₦1,245,000.00) to be deducted exclusively from the gross worth of recovered assets upon successful clearing and settlement.
Submission Feedback: Submitting this finalized layer triggers a clean system success box stating: "Asset Recovery Request Successfully Submitted. Your request has been queued and is currently appearing on the compliance dashboard for official administrative review and clearing validation." Includes a primary CTA button pointing back to dashboard.html.
